description:
Update to the mirador Valle de la Samaria: Now, you‘ll find the beautiful litle new hotel with 3 rooms and 1 suite (all rooms with shower). The suite is separated on his own level in front of the restaurant, very private and with nice view. You can park your car near the restaurant and stay over night in your own car, use the bathroom and restaurant. You can also make a guided tour to the Bosque de Palma de Sera with Juan-José.  Today, we where alone and John drove to San Felix to get some food to cook dinner for us, we could chose what we wanted to eat. Very nice place, nice few, nice people! 3G.
@ecohotelvalledelasamaria
+57 314 522 1604

We sleep here for 3 nights. one of the few straight places to park and sleep, since the town is practically all on a slope.

We felt very safe here, very quiet and calm street. You also can park here and walk to the main square without worrying!

@wheelsonthewild

Very good spot for spending the night in Manizales. 

One of the best parts of the city. The spot is located in a very quiet and safe residential street. Some people walking their dogs during the morning, very good vibes and totally recommended! 

@wheelsonthewild
